                      Musicians on celluloid                    Films Division, Government of India, and Nandan, West Bengal Film Centre host the screening of documentaries on great Indian music composers. Anil Biswas (dir: Brij Bhusan; 6 pm) sketches the life and works of the music legend, whose songs graced films from 1935 to 1965. Pankaj Mullicks evergreen songs come alive during his talk about his musical journey in Pankaj Mullick (dir: Bharat Dholakia; 6.25 pm). Naushad Ali  The Melody Continues (dir: Buddhadeb Dasgupta; 6.45 pm) pays tribute to one of the greatest music directors of Indian cinema. Salil Chowdhury (dir: Jagadish Banerjee; 7.20 pm) presents a brilliant portrait of the multi-faceted music genius.            Event: Screening of films on four Indian music composers When: Today; 6 pm onwards Where: Nandan II	                    
